Package leeLogger

Class Logger

java.lang.Object
leeLogger.Logger
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, Loggable
public abstract class Logger
extends java.lang.Object
implements Loggable, java.io.Serializable
Abstract Class specified in broad outline that a class that extends this class should log data from a user and store data on a database The Logger abstract specifies in broad outline what the functions are that a class that inherits from the Logger abstract class should be able to perform. These include being able to log data to a database, and read data from a user. The data is specified as type Transactions in this case or any of the subclasses of a Transactions parent class.
Author:
leefowler student at SDA8 (KTH Stockholm)
